The need for speed The Run is disputed throughout America.
Revision
Originally a hassle-free race is transformed due to a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with it in a routine morning trip to work.
It fulfills everyone’s ambition to some extent, but it’s useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new subtitled The Run produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already aged Need for Speed racing series and to release a kind of game from playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be during which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what we expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the set pulls down due to some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of an incomprehensible laziness on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught up in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to settle them starts to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The itinerary is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
As a result, each race is done on a different route and the planned stages in different environments that are quite different from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are quite nice, even if the graphical technical level is the same as the previous series.
After all, this is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumnal landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very visually pleasant.
The tests are in addition from time to time embellished with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you need to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
In addition, the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classical duel with the chronometer) and then another duel awaits you with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and try to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the off-vehicle passages.
Rather, it’s an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help them by tapping on the right button at the right time.
It's nothing complicated.
What’s surprising is that there are fewer moments like this than you expect (to be specific, there are only three).
The result is like this because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the gameplay.
The pattern of behavior is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that there is currently nothing extraordinary, but it cannot be said to be negative.
When it comes to realistic simulation, you’ll have to look elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not yet in place.
We do not expect from this game a complicated deformation and collisions, but when you do not have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, so it is not completely good.
During tight overtakings, you sometimes touch each other slightly, but otherwise your car is in a frenzy.
Or it ends up in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really upsets you.
The restart is done so that when you have broken your figure or you have come out in the set the game takes you back at the time of the last point on the itinerary.
But you only have 5 restarts.
Once you have used the 5 restarts you must restart the game from the beginning.
It is therefore more a tool, in case something is not going well, than something you can really rely on.
Sometimes reboots don't help and you have to find the solution by remembering the itinerary in question.
The great thing about this game is that the same actions end up in the same places.
For example, there are certain corners that you have to go through in a certain way otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise, you will encounter in a given place "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or one minute late.
What annoys you are the situations when you see the opponent easily pass between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you either have to stand aside and contour them or brake.
It does not matter if you go in front of him because it is "calculated"in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This annoys the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long deck in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides your view of the other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a lot of times.
One can understand that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and adrenaline-filled, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it is a pity because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you do not have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn't matter if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is to change the car during the races.
You have to be careful about gasoline pumps on the routes because you can change cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, U.S. highways for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic surroundings on highly technical drives such as lace roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are racing in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main regime of history.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that are added to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
This connects online with the Autolog feature which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other features in the community.
One of the most difficult shots to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (looks like it) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (looks like it).
Your speed indicator shows you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you is a subway raft that sends the car directly to the garbage.
At the editorial we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about creating this game or whether the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally nice and in some cases really great.
What bothers me is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This is especially true for accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imagery is no longer useful for you.
The sound part is good and the track is a choice.
In order to please the largest number and especially the youngest audience a new soundtrack was created in the style of "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Need for Speed: The Run is really confusing.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that it is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it is not finished.
The fun is really good but prepare for the mistakes to hit you in the eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
Velvet students in concert with Charles University choirs
The Festa Academica festival proposes for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of high schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts held on 17 November.
"Charles University has an important role to play in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Education and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizer team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes that takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening, the concert "Students of velvet" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady, during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University are performing.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate with dignity the International Students’ Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Choirs in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
The whole action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, monthly meetings, student happenings and other activities.
Interested parties can find all the information on the festival's website www.festaacademica.cz.
