As for those who have committed assisted suicide, 41% of respondents believe that they should not be prosecuted.
When it comes to maintaining or discontinuing care with a patient, the situation is less clear, say the authors of the report.
Also, in the list of their recommendations, they suggest that it should be stated in the Criminal Code that the withdrawal of care for which there has been a legally valid refusal is not criminal.
